Sentencas: Solid oxide fuel cell (SOFC) electrodes, after a high temperature sintering, may be impregnated to deposit nanoparticles within their pores to enhance the catalytic function.
Titulo: Effect of samarium doped ceria nanoparticles impregnation on the performance of anode supported SOFC with (Pr0.7Ca0.3)0.9MnO3-δcathode

Sentencas: Samarium doped CeO2 (SDC) nanoparticles were infiltrated into (Pr0.7Ca0.3)(0.9)MnO3-delta (PCM) cathode of anode supported SOFC cells.
Titulo: Effect of samarium doped ceria nanoparticles impregnation on the performance of anode supported SOFC with (Pr0.7Ca0.3)0.9MnO3-δcathode
Effect of samarium doped ceria nanoparticles impregnation on the performance of anode supported SOFC with (Pr0.7Ca0.3)0.9MnO3-δcathode

Sentencas: SDC impregnated in cathode showed the maximum power density of 580 mW/cm(2) compared with 310 mW/cm(2) of the cell without impregnation at 850 degrees C.
Titulo: Effect of samarium doped ceria nanoparticles impregnation on the performance of anode supported SOFC with (Pr0.7Ca0.3)0.9MnO3-δcathode

Sentencas: The cells were also characterized with the impedance spectra, and the SDC impregnation significantly reduced the polarization resistance.
Titulo: Effect of samarium doped ceria nanoparticles impregnation on the performance of anode supported SOFC with (Pr0.7Ca0.3)0.9MnO3-δcathode

Sentencas: After performance test the cells were characterized with scanning electron microscopy (SEM), and the cathode morphology showed the impregnated SDC particles were nanosized and were deposited on the surface of the PCM framework.
Titulo: Effect of samarium doped ceria nanoparticles impregnation on the performance of anode supported SOFC with (Pr0.7Ca0.3)0.9MnO3-δcathode

Sentencas: The possible mechanism for the performance improvement was discussed.
Titulo: Effect of samarium doped ceria nanoparticles impregnation on the performance of anode supported SOFC with (Pr0.7Ca0.3)0.9MnO3-δcathode
